======================
Multi-questions Survey
======================

This is a multi-questions-survey web program based on Django. It is similar with the default tutorials of Django -- Django-polls, but it can handle more than one question in one survey paper.

Dependencies
------------
Django (http://djangoproject.com)


Install
-------
1. Add "survey" to your INSTALLED_APPS setting like this::

      INSTALLED_APPS = (
          ...
          'survey',
      )

2. Include the blog URLconf in your project urls.py like this::

      url(r'^survey/', include('survey.urls')),

3. Run `python manage.py syncdb` to create the blog models.

4. Start the development server and visit http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/
  to manage your survey papers. (you'll need the Admin app enabled).

5. Visit http://127.0.0.1:8000/survey to visit your survey website.

6. For more general setup tutorials of Django, such as database, admin page, please visit: https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.5/

